Package: INCOMMON
Title: INCOMMON: Inference of Copy Number and Mutation Multiplicity in Oncology
Version: 0.1.0
Maintainer: Nicola Calonaci <nicola.calonaci@gmail.com>
Authors@R:
    c(person("Nicola", "Calonaci", , "nicola.calonaci@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2721-4888")),
    person("Giulio", "Caravagna", , "gcaravagn@gmail.com", role = "aut",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4240-3265")))
Description: Implements the statistical framework described in Calonaci
    et al. (2024) <doi:10.1101/2024.05.13.24307238> to infer mutation copy
    number and multiplicity directly from tumour-only clinical targeted
    sequencing data, without requiring matched normal samples. This
    information is used to derive gene mutant dosage, an emergent property
    of the interplay between somatic mutations and copy-number alterations
    that is overlooked by standard binary mutant/wild-type models. The
    package provides functions to stratify patients by mutant dosage of
    oncogenes and tumour suppressor genes, and to identify biomarkers of
    prognosis and metastatic tropism.
